  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "This is partially copied off of the old repo issue 101 : https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle-contract/issues/101\r\n\r\n## Expected behaviour\r\n\r\n`send()` should optionally consume a `tx_params` object.\r\n\r\n## Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nThe contract.js `send()` function doesn't accept a `tx_params` object.\r\n\r\nThis is unintuitive since almost every other function provided does accept a `tx_params` object. Due to the nature of JS, no errors or warnings are given, making this a potential source of nasty bugs.\r\n\r\nIn Web3.js the `send()` function takes a `tx_params` object which makes truffle's `send()` behavior really confusing. \r\n\r\n## Documentation\r\n\r\n`send()` and `sendTransaction()` (which takes a  `tx_params` !) are not documented. \r\nThis makes the issue really frustrating and hard to fix. Basically you have to find someone who already had the problem.",
